1
00:00:04,491 --> 00:00:07,479
I remember, once, I heard 
 

2
00:00:07,479 --> 00:00:12,984
that the world’s leading
authority on Hinduism, so-called,

3
00:00:12,984 --> 00:00:17,347
who would like write 
the encyclopedia entry.

4
00:00:17,575 --> 00:00:21,311
Now it’s Wikipedia, 
but in the old days …

5
00:00:21,311 --> 00:00:24,885
You can read about it online,
[Laughing]

6
00:00:24,885 --> 00:00:27,058
people had books
and libraries,

7
00:00:27,058 --> 00:00:29,277
and these things 
called encyclopedias.

8
00:00:29,359 --> 00:00:32,516
[I am God?]

9
00:00:32,930 --> 00:00:35,347
And so he would write 
like that section.

10
00:00:35,347 --> 00:00:39,067
His name was A.L. Basham,
he wrote a book called 
 

11
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:41,166
“The Wonder that was India”,
anyway …

12
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:43,617
So he was giving a lecture 
at UCLA,

13
00:00:43,617 --> 00:00:45,578
University of California, 
Los Angeles.

14
00:00:45,578 --> 00:00:51,088
I thought I would go meet him,
see what he was saying.

15
00:00:51,485 --> 00:00:54,111
I could see
what was sweet about him,

16
00:00:54,111 --> 00:00:57,823
this stodgy old British gentleman—

17
00:00:57,823 --> 00:01:02,012
he was really a closet Krishnaite,

18
00:01:02,012 --> 00:01:05,651
in his heart, you could really see,
he was a devotee.

19
00:01:05,651 --> 00:01:10,104
And one of the things I thought
he said was very sweet.

20
00:01:10,197 --> 00:01:13,442
At first he was talking about
different gods and goddesses,

21
00:01:13,442 --> 00:01:16,671
like we’ve heard Mark Twain:
Huckleberry Finn, Tom Sawyer.

22
00:01:16,671 --> 00:01:24,071
He said, “In religion
India is the only millionaire.

23
00:01:24,071 --> 00:01:26,863
All the other religions
are paupers in comparison,

24
00:01:26,863 --> 00:01:28,155
India is the only millionaire.”

25
00:01:28,155 --> 00:01:31,328
Meaning, millions of gods 
and goddesses.

26
00:01:31,328 --> 00:01:33,562
So, he gave a slide show 
and he said,

27
00:01:33,562 --> 00:01:36,107
“And they’re making more.”

28
00:01:37,061 --> 00:01:39,881
Just like we have Kṛṣṇa
with the Dasavatars,

29
00:01:39,881 --> 00:01:42,342
Kṛṣṇa in the centre
and the ten Avatars round,

30
00:01:42,342 --> 00:01:48,398
they showed one Shram Devata,
the Goddess of Technology.

31
00:01:48,398 --> 00:01:52,469
And they showed like in the ten things:
a rocket ship, a tractor,

32
00:01:52,469 --> 00:01:56,839
all these technological things,
and she’s there. [Laughing]

33
00:01:56,839 --> 00:01:59,575
Then there was Santoshi Ma,

34
00:01:59,575 --> 00:02:02,848
who was a goddess 
created in Bollywood.

35
00:02:02,848 --> 00:02:06,576
Then all these simple-hearted people
went to see the movie,

36
00:02:06,576 --> 00:02:08,658
and they showed this goddess,
Santoshi Ma,

37
00:02:08,658 --> 00:02:10,104
and here’s how 
you worship her,

38
00:02:10,104 --> 00:02:13,192
this is her mantra,
this is her pūjā paraphenalia ...

39
00:02:13,192 --> 00:02:19,570
All over India people started
worshiping Santoshi Ma. [Laughing]

40
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:23,633
Like the lady … 
Gurudev said, in Calcutta, one lady

41
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:27,936
who was offering dandavats 
to so many stones,

42
00:02:27,936 --> 00:02:29,684
and they go, 
“Didi, what are you doing?”

43
00:02:29,684 --> 00:02:32,231
And she said, 
“One of them might be Śiva.”

44
00:02:32,231 --> 00:02:35,231
[Laughing]

45
00:02:35,231 --> 00:02:36,168
So,

46
00:02:37,968 --> 00:02:44,137
when A.L. Basham
came to the subject of māyāvād,

47
00:02:46,384 --> 00:02:52,611
the ultimate God-delusion 
that “I am God”—

48
00:02:52,611 --> 00:02:55,069
“I am God,
you are God”,

49
00:02:55,069 --> 00:02:57,588
or as John Lennon
even mocked

50
00:02:57,588 --> 00:03:00,019
in the beginning 
of “I am the Walrus”,

51
00:03:00,019 --> 00:03:06,900
“I am he as you are he as you are me,
And we are all together.”

52
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:13,351
So, on this subject
A.L. Basham said,
 

53
00:03:13,841 --> 00:03:16,866
“I am you?”
He said,

54
00:03:16,866 --> 00:03:21,863
“I don’t know quite frankly
if I want to be you.”

55
00:03:21,863 --> 00:03:23,943
[Laughing]

56
00:03:23,943 --> 00:03:27,591
In one sentence he showed
how silly that whole idea was.

